File: COVID-19 test. AFP/Jens Schlueter JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 17,958 new COVID-19 cases. The NICD said 157 COVID-19 related deaths have also been recorded. READ: Delta variant more transmissible: expert This brings total fatalities to 59,778 to date. Gauteng continues to account for the majority of infections, with 11,303 cases in the last 24 hours. A total of 70,067 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours.